      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 17
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_6",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Hey there! I\u2019m parting ways with my trusty ride, and honestly, it\u2019s been such a joy to drive. It\u2019s in really solid shape and has been super well-maintained, so it\u2019s ready to hit the road with you right away! Whether you\u2019re commuting or heading out on a weekend trip, this car handles like a dream. Come take it for a spin\u2014you\u2019re going to love how it feels!",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 17
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant equipped with VarioCam Plus, delivering a linear 320hp. This example is paired with a 6-speed manual transaxle, offering precise engagement and mechanical tactile feedback. The chassis dynamics are defined by its rear-engine layout, utilizing MacPherson struts and a sophisticated multi-link rear suspension for superior corner-exit traction. Crucial preventative maintenance has been addressed, including an IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal (RMS) replacement. The braking system features four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors, ensuring fade-resistant deceleration. While the exterior and interior exhibit minor honest wear consistent with a well-maintained driver-tier vehicle, the powertrain and drivetrain remain high-functioning and track-ready. A compelling opportunity for an enthusiast seeking a mechanically verified 911 with optimal power-to-weight ratios.",
